בו  ב / Shabbat of holiness. This original Hebrew text addresses Shabbat in feminine
language, as bride and as queen. She is the subject of our affection and the
source of our sustenance. We ask that her blessing dwell in our midst for
peace and joy. We ask, too, that the Jewish people bless Shabbat with their
love and devotion.    /SC/XXM.P./XX/PR

