for all Israel, and for all who dwell on earth. And say: Amen./PR

/SCK/XXAVANAH./XX Adding the rabbinic phrase "/ITveòal kol yoshvey tevel/XX" (and for all
who dwell on earth) logically completes the concentric circles of our
aspirations--our care starts with our minyan, extends to the entire Jewish
people, and radiates outward from there to all who share our planet./PR

